curlPythonJavaScriptReact <pre><code># Get latest news
curl https://free-crypto-news.vercel.app/api/news

# Get AI summary
curl https://free-crypto-news.vercel.app/api/digest
</code></pre> <pre><code>import requests

news = requests.get("https://free-crypto-news.vercel.app/api/news").json()

for article in news["articles"][:5]:
    print(f"📰 {article['title']}")
</code></pre> <pre><code>const response = await fetch('https://free-crypto-news.vercel.app/api/news');
const { articles } = await response.json();

articles.slice(0, 5).forEach(article =&gt; {
  console.log(`📰 ${article.title}`);
});
</code></pre> <pre><code>import { useCryptoNews } from '@free-crypto-news/react';

function NewsFeed() {
  const { articles, loading } = useCryptoNews();

  if (loading) return &lt;p&gt;Loading...&lt;/p&gt;;

  return articles.map(a =&gt; &lt;Article key={a.id} {...a} /&gt;);
}
</code></pre>

Endpoint Method Purpose Details <code>/api/i18n/translate</code> POST On-demand translation Groq-powered translation for dynamic content. Supports single text or batch translations to 18 locales <code>/api/news/international</code> GET International news Fetches from Korean, Chinese, Japanese, Spanish sources with optional translation <code>/api/openapi.json</code> GET OpenAPI spec Returns complete OpenAPI 3.1.0 specification for API documentation/integrations <p><code>/api/i18n/translate</code> Details: - Authentication: None (relies on Groq API key) - Rate limit: Subject to Groq limits - Request format:   </p><pre><code>{
  "text": "Hello world",
  "targetLocale": "es",
  "context": "button label"
}
</code></pre> - Batch format:   <pre><code>{
  "texts": { "key1": "Hello", "key2": "World" },
  "targetLocale": "es"
}
</code></pre><p></p> <p><code>/api/news/international</code> Details: - Parameters: <code>language</code> (ko|zh|ja|es|all), <code>translate</code> (bool), <code>limit</code>, <code>region</code> (asia|europe|latam|all) - Caching: 5 minutes (revalidate=300) - Runtime: Edge</p>
